Well, that was nuts. This recipe should have been named something like how to incinerate dinner without even trying. There is no need to cook chicken thighs at 500 degrees. Do what the smart people on this page (not me) have done and brown the chicken in a skillet and cook at a more normal temperature for more time. I ended up with barely cooked chicken, incinerated roast asparagus, black lemon slices (the ones on top; the ones underneath the chicken were fine and were the only good thing about this recipe), a smoky kitchen, greasy oven... there is really no need. The recipe is not all that wonderful.

